{"code":0,"message":"","data":null,"sentence":{"phonemes":[],"text":"Everyone who has tasted me has died. I feel the passage of time, the cruelty of nature. I walk alone through an endless dark night, with only the rain to cleanse me. The moon warms at midnight's third watch. At high noon, a crescent moon hangs. And I am merely the most ordinary among thousands upon thousands of mushrooms. Why do you speak to me?","words":[]}}
